00:02:34,345 --> 00:02:45,748
Announcements, accolades, remembrances, reports, and records 26096 offered by President Behrs be it resolved by the Medford City Council that we offer condolences to the family and friends of Mimi Gordon and commemorate her life.

24
00:02:46,388 --> 00:02:56,411
Mimi was a long-time member of the Medford Democratic City Committee and Ward 8 Democratic Committee, tireless union representative with SEIU 509, public servant, campaign worker, and party activist.

25
00:02:56,851 --> 00:02:59,652
She was a beloved member of the Medford community, and we will miss her.

26
00:03:00,732 --> 00:03:01,772
Any councilors want to speak?

27
00:03:03,373 --> 00:03:03,973
Councilor Singh.

28
00:03:06,228 --> 00:03:08,250
Mimi was a true leader in our community.

29
00:03:09,371 --> 00:03:14,715
She's one of the first people who I met when I was campaigning for this position.

30
00:03:14,915 --> 00:03:20,039
And through her knowledge, experience, her passion, I've learned so much.

31
00:03:20,099 --> 00:03:28,446
And I think counselors, I don't want to speak for everyone, but I'm sure counselors abound will say that they have learned so much.

32
00:03:30,917 --> 00:03:46,256
We've been able to do a lot, and I think what people don't necessarily always see is that behind the things we do as a city council, there's always a community, and there's always people who are driving the effort, who are making us do better.

33
00:03:47,120 --> 00:03:52,965
making us learn about issues, making us better counselors too.

34
00:03:53,225 --> 00:03:54,867
And Mimi was one of those people.

35
00:03:56,028 --> 00:03:57,068
She'll be dearly missed.

36
00:03:57,909 --> 00:04:01,952
And I want to just convey my deepest condolences.

37
00:04:03,814 --> 00:04:04,875
Thank you, Councilor Sang.

38
00:04:04,935 --> 00:04:05,576
Councilor Lemming.

39
00:04:06,857 --> 00:04:09,879
Thank you, Council President, for this resolution.

40
00:04:09,919 --> 00:04:12,521
So I'll say that I

41
00:04:15,542 --> 00:04:23,790
I didn't know Mimi too well myself, but I know a lot of people who knew her and were influenced her through the Ward 8 Democratic Committee.

42
00:04:24,430 --> 00:04:33,479
She spent over 20 years organizing that committee, recruiting members across the ward and really

43
00:04:35,781 --> 00:04:41,906
revitalizing it in the long time that she spent as committee chair.

44
00:04:42,306 --> 00:04:49,732
And a lot of the folks, a lot of folks reached out to me about this.

45
00:04:50,093 --> 00:04:53,496
And to echo my colleague, councilor saying,

46
00:04:55,257 --> 00:05:03,987
are so many people who add so much to the scene by what they do behind the scenes.

47
00:05:04,208 --> 00:05:14,259
There's like any anytime you see political organization, anytime you see city councilors, anytime you see, you know, people that are sort of in front of the crowd giving speeches.

48
00:05:15,120 --> 00:05:29,125
is there are even more people who quietly do the work of recruiting people talking to them one on one organizing and Mimi was a person who did that in spades over a very, very long period of time.

49
00:05:29,686 --> 00:05:35,088
And so it's no surprise to me that she touched so many people within a

50
00:05:35,948 --> 00:05:39,550
uh, within the Democratic Party, especially, especially here in Medford.

51
00:05:39,830 --> 00:05:43,352
So, uh, thank you again for this, for this resolution.

52
00:05:43,392 --> 00:05:45,413
And this was, this was a real loss to our community.

53
00:05:47,475 --> 00:05:48,515
Thank you, Councilor Lemming.

54
00:05:48,535 --> 00:05:56,900
Um, Mimi was someone who I've known for, um, maybe more than 10 years.

55
00:05:57,600 --> 00:06:00,362
And I think, you know, she represents

56
00:06:02,110 --> 00:06:05,373
some of the most important values that we could have as a community.

57
00:06:05,573 --> 00:06:12,639
She's a kind person, a principled person, a passionate person, and an engaged person.

58
00:06:12,759 --> 00:06:27,331
She was very devoted to the labor movement, to unions and workers, to local politics, to thinking globally, acting locally,

59
00:06:29,919 --> 00:06:53,427
And more than anything, she was just someone that you really enjoyed talking to, whether it was about things going on here in Medford, or things going on state, federal politics, local state Democratic Party, or just her love for her family, her friends, her community, and the people around her.

60
00:06:53,547 --> 00:06:54,288
I think she had a...

61
00:06:58,877 --> 00:07:01,179
She believed in people.

62
00:07:01,319 --> 00:07:04,141
She believed in the human spirit.

63
00:07:04,221 --> 00:07:08,845
And I think she fought very hard to just try to help her fellow neighbor.

64
00:07:09,165 --> 00:07:17,052
And she certainly inspired me on more than one occasion to maybe

65
00:07:18,043 --> 00:07:25,467
speak a little louder or fight a little harder or talk to someone who maybe I hadn't considered talking to before.

66
00:07:25,947 --> 00:07:29,429
And I've missed her actually already these past couple of years.

67
00:07:29,629 --> 00:07:36,353
She's had some health issues and to lose her is a major loss for our community.

68
00:07:36,553 --> 00:07:43,717
So I'm thankful for everything she did, for all the people that she influenced, for all the people that she lifted up.

69
00:07:44,497 --> 00:07:46,739
and that we can celebrate her tonight.

70
00:07:46,759 --> 00:07:50,463
And I know there's some folks here who maybe wanna say a few words about Mimi as well.

71
00:07:50,623 --> 00:07:57,950
So we will turn the floor over to members of the public now who might wanna share a few words about Mimi Gordon.

72
00:08:14,588 --> 00:08:16,589
I'm Barry Ingber, 9 Draper Street.

73
00:08:17,870 --> 00:08:21,892
And I was a friend of Mimi's for over 40 years.

74
00:08:22,392 --> 00:08:26,855
And she was a very committed and kind person.

75
00:08:28,135 --> 00:08:31,377
She was both gentle and fierce.

76
00:08:32,658 --> 00:08:41,282
And she built community wherever she went, at every level, from her condo to the labor union to the city of Medford to the Democratic Party.

77
00:08:44,075 --> 00:09:03,504
I think as people have intimated, she's the kind of person who I think many people in the community will miss without even knowing that we miss her because she accomplished a lot very quietly.

78
00:09:05,405 --> 00:09:05,765
Thank you.

79
00:09:07,626 --> 00:09:08,007
Thank you.

80
00:09:09,847 --> 00:09:12,749
Is there anyone else who'd like to speak at this time about me?

81
00:09:17,563 --> 00:09:18,103
Seeing none.

82
00:09:18,123 --> 00:09:22,686
Oh, we have someone on Zoom.

83
00:09:22,926 --> 00:09:25,067
I will recognize Munir Jermanis.

84
00:09:31,130 --> 00:09:34,252
Munir Jermanis, Three Summits Road.

85
00:09:35,853 --> 00:09:41,676
I met Mimi primarily through people power.

86
00:09:43,533 --> 00:09:54,419
She was, as everybody mentioned, a quietly active, gentle individual, a woman of principle.

87
00:09:55,860 --> 00:09:58,801
And I, for one, will certainly miss her presence.

88
00:09:59,442 --> 00:09:59,802
Thank you.

89
00:10:01,663 --> 00:10:02,103
Thank you.

90
00:10:06,405 --> 00:10:08,527
And I'll recognize now Matt Sampson on Zoom.

91
00:10:08,627 --> 00:10:11,148
Matt, name and address for the record, please.

92
00:10:13,868 --> 00:10:17,453
Yeah, I'm Matt Sampson, 131 Winchester Street, Brookline.

93
00:10:17,473 --> 00:10:18,675
I'm Mimi Gordon's nephew.

94
00:10:19,436 --> 00:10:29,990
I moved to Boston seven years ago and only got to know Mimi over the past seven years with the depth that many of you have known her for years and decades.

95
00:10:30,993 --> 00:10:35,215
The past couple of years, as some of you have alluded to, were somewhat difficult for Mimi.

96
00:10:35,355 --> 00:10:39,057
Her world became smaller as she lost some physical mobility.

97
00:10:39,757 --> 00:10:46,261
But I want to assure those folks listening on Zoom and those of you here representing Medford that she thought about you often.

98
00:10:46,901 --> 00:10:59,950
the issues that she brought to the floor over the decades, the fights that she fought were still deep within her, and she valued a civic discourse, the political process, and all of you members of the Medford Council.

99
00:11:00,190 --> 00:11:07,455
And I just want to thank you for giving her a place, a community, and an outlet for the vast amounts of energy she had over decades.

100
00:11:08,075 --> 00:11:10,937
She set a real role model, a role model for

101
00:11:11,997 --> 00:11:21,805
her family, her nieces, her nephews, and now her little grandnieces and nephews, Lily, age 17, Addie, age two, Arlo, eight months.

102
00:11:22,405 --> 00:11:32,974
They knew an aunt who, while small and somewhat diminished physically, was strong and bright and a role model for those of us who want to participate in civic discourse.

103
00:11:33,014 --> 00:11:33,614
Thank you very much.

104
00:11:36,116 --> 00:11:37,217
Matt, thank you so much.

105
00:11:37,297 --> 00:11:38,938
And our condolences to your family.

106
00:11:39,479 --> 00:11:40,800
And may her memory be a blessing.

107
