271
00:24:14,312 --> 00:24:18,573
But the other thing that you mentioned, Chris, about proximity to where people are.

272
00:24:19,694 --> 00:24:31,182
in early recovery, how important it is to have access to groups like this or maybe a doctor or a facility where you can go to get the kind of help that you need.

273
00:24:31,462 --> 00:24:37,186
So it's just something that I like to repeat and remind people that it is really important to have access to the

274
00:24:38,027 --> 00:24:50,011
assistive medications, assistive services, and community groups that can help people when they're in those early stages because that can be the difference between being able to stay in recovery or not.

275
00:24:50,491 --> 00:24:56,053
If you have to drive somewhere far away and you're trying to keep your job and you're trying to keep your family together, all that stuff can be really difficult.

276
00:24:56,113 --> 00:25:00,635
So anything that we can do to continue helping the people in Medford that need help I think is really important.

277
00:25:01,655 --> 00:25:10,104
