00:58:51,591 --> 00:58:52,772
Motions, orders, and resolutions.

779
00:58:52,792 --> 00:58:59,376
26-101, offered by Councilor Sang, resolution to amend the Code of Ordinances, Section 14-315, do not knock, registry Councilor Sang.

780
00:59:01,994 --> 00:59:13,920
A resident reached out to me and she had said that she'd registered for our NONOC registry, but that solicitors kept coming and she was worried about a number of things.

781
00:59:14,660 --> 00:59:20,143
I think at the end of the day, it's about having peace and quiet at home in your neighborhood.

782
00:59:21,917 --> 00:59:24,018
she wanted to know why the registry wasn't working.

783
00:59:24,359 --> 00:59:35,206
So in reading the ordinance text and then last week in the chambers, Clerk Alicio and I talked about it a little bit.

784
00:59:36,687 --> 00:59:42,311
There's a kind of miscommunication in City Hall, or it's really with the police department.

785
00:59:43,645 --> 00:59:46,908
And there's some kind of gaps in our ordinance as well.

786
00:59:47,549 --> 00:59:52,934
And I looked at what a more modernized ordinance would look like and what this ordinance looks like.

787
00:59:54,275 --> 00:59:56,357
And there are, I think, about three gaps.

788
00:59:56,938 --> 01:00:02,904
First one being that the registry's given to solicitors when they get their license and only then.

789
01:00:03,424 --> 01:00:05,466
So if you register next week,

790
01:00:08,025 --> 01:00:12,288
Every solicitor licensed last month has a list that doesn't include you.

791
01:00:12,308 --> 01:00:13,710
So they're not getting up-to-date lists.

792
01:00:14,790 --> 01:00:18,213
And no one's violating the ordinance, it's just that the list that they have is old.

793
01:00:19,274 --> 01:00:24,658
The second gap is that the enforcement falls on the individual canvasser and not the company.

794
01:00:24,718 --> 01:00:28,601
So that's a kind of mismatch with other municipalities.

795
01:00:30,542 --> 01:00:35,726
So a canvasser who gets that fine, if they were to get a fine,

796
01:00:36,525 --> 01:00:45,470
would then go back to their employer and then tell them about it, but then nothing would happen to the company, so there's no kind of impact on the company, who should be the ones responsible there.

797
01:00:46,151 --> 01:00:56,537
And then there's a third gap in unlicensed solicitors, where people could be operating in the city without a license at all, which they really should be having, and

798
01:00:57,412 --> 01:01:02,075
our ordinance is actually just silent about whether they're bound by the registry or not.

799
01:01:02,435 --> 01:01:03,916
The answer right now is unclear.

800
01:01:04,557 --> 01:01:11,001
So the proposals in the resolution closes the three gaps that I've mentioned.

801
01:01:11,621 --> 01:01:19,506
They're trying to, the goal I think is to update the registry a bit more and increase communication between

802
01:01:20,891 --> 01:01:27,516
here and to the police department, which is oftentimes where the solicitors and businesses go for their lists.

803
01:01:29,782 --> 01:01:40,104
And so for me, in my opinion, this is a small procedural fix that tries to get at what we have tried, what we're trying to do.

804
01:01:41,625 --> 01:01:50,667
But I'm happy to hear from counselors about what we think our next steps should be, whether we refer this to a committee or whether we pass it.

805
01:01:51,187 --> 01:01:56,928
I know I'd also like to invite Clerk Lucio to provide any kind of

806
01:01:57,648 --> 01:01:59,832
input or any ideas that you might have.

807
01:02:00,573 --> 01:02:01,875
But I don't want to put you on the spot.

808
01:02:05,280 --> 01:02:06,282
Thank you, Councilor Sang.

809
01:02:06,342 --> 01:02:07,023
Councilor Malauulu.

810
01:02:09,903 --> 01:02:11,144
Thank you for putting this together.

811
01:02:11,244 --> 01:02:17,607
I appreciate, you know, responding to a direct constituent complaint on this.

812
01:02:18,147 --> 01:02:22,249
I was wondering if it could be possible to move it to committee.

813
01:02:22,390 --> 01:02:24,471
I had some questions on some of the amendments.

814
01:02:26,011 --> 01:02:32,755
On the amendment, too, about the employer liability for employee violations in terms

815
