It looks like if they made, if there's one person that does it, that it's a one-year license revocation, and that just seems maybe a bit extreme or a bit harsh on the first try, maybe there could be a way to look at that and try to see if there's,

816
01:02:52,312 --> 01:02:53,653
a second or third or something.

817
01:02:53,673 --> 01:02:55,033
It just seems like a very harsh.

818
01:02:55,634 --> 01:03:05,818
And then the third one was just on the amendment around the imposing a $300 per offense fine on it.

819
01:03:06,579 --> 01:03:11,501
I was just curious, like, who would be in charge of collecting that?

820
01:03:11,561 --> 01:03:12,682
Like, where would that lie?

821
01:03:12,782 --> 01:03:15,223
How would that kind of figure itself out?

822
01:03:15,263 --> 01:03:21,666
So I don't know if that's something here to answer those questions or to look at it at committee, just to kind of flesh some of that out in there.

823
01:03:24,981 --> 01:03:29,562
up.

824
